=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 16, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uzu1665702542108.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uzu1665702542108.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uzu1665702542108.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uzu1665702542108\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n DBMS Connector Overview\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"uzu1665702542108__dbms_connector_overview_142726\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This section provides an overview of supported functionality and limitations for all DBMS connectors.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzu1665702542108__p_d47411e1_d47412e1_d47413e1\">Each Uniface database connector is identified in Uniface by a 3-character mnemonic, and each one has its own set of limits, SQL scripts and utilities, and properties that you can configure using the DBMS options provided.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzu1665702542108__p_d47414e1_d47415e1_d47416e1\">For the supported platforms and product versions for your\n         DBMS, refer to the <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://community.rocketsoftware.com/rocket-uniface-forum-home-20/uniface-product-availability-information-18191\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Availability Matrix</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzu1665702542108__p_d47420e1_d47421e1_d47422e1\">The connector mnemonic is used in assignment files to designate the connector version, the path to the connector, and the options to be used. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"msq1665702542189.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/msq1665702542189.html\" title=\"Use the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file to specify the database and component engine connectors used, and their parameter options. The options available depend on the connector in use.\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sbg1665702735473.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sbg1665702735473.html\" title=\"A path is a named route to a resource required by the application, such as a database connector and database, a remote server, or a file location.\">Paths and Path Assignments</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Connector Mnemonics</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Connector Mnemonic</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Database</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">DB2</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">DB2. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bpq1665702735544.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bpq1665702735544.html\" title=\"The DB2 database connector enables you to integrate DB2 databases with Uniface.\">DB2</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">INF</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Informix. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"byb1665702735623.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/byb1665702735623.html\" title=\"The Informix DBMS connector enables you to integrate Informix databases with Uniface.\">Informix</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">LDP</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">LDAP Connector. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mcs1665702735695.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mcs1665702735695.html\" title=\"The Uniface LDAP connector enables you to connect with LDAP servers, including stand-alone LDAP servers and X.500 Directory System Agents with an LDAP gateway installed.\">LDAP Connector</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">MSS</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Microsoft SQL Server. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pda1665702735767.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pda1665702735767.html\" title=\"The Microsoft SQL Server DBMS connector (MSS) enables you to integrate MS SQL databases with Uniface.\">Microsoft SQL Server</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">MQL</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">MySQL. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bhn1665702735843.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bhn1665702735843.html\" title=\"The MySQL DBMS connector enables you to integrate MySQL databases with Uniface.\">MySQL</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">OD0, OD1, OD2</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">ODBC. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aly1665702736004.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aly1665702736004.html\" title=\"The ODBC DBMS connector enables you to integrate ODBC databases with Uniface.\">ODBC</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">ORA</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Oracle. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tdz1665702736077.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tdz1665702736077.html\" title=\"The Oracle DBMS connector enables you to integrate Oracle databases with Uniface.\">Oracle</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">PGS</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">PostgreSQL. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qlo1665702736148.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qlo1665702736148.html\">PostgreSQL</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">SEQ</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Sequential. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zyg1665702736223.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zyg1665702736223.html\" title=\"The SEQ connector enables you to integrate sequential file access with Uniface.\">Sequential</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">SLE</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">SQLite. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xxz1665702736293.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xxz1665702736293.html\" title=\"SQLite (SLE) is the default database provided for the Uniface Repository and is appropriate for single-user use. It is not recommended for a shared Uniface Repository.\">SQLite</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">SYB</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Sybase. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ifw1665702736363.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifw1665702736363.html\" title=\"The Sybase DBMS connector enables you to integrate Sybase databases with Uniface.\">Sybase</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">TXT</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uzu1665702542108__table_d4430e1_d4431e1_d4432e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Text. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"twr1665702736437.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/twr1665702736437.html\" title=\"The TXT connector enables you to read and write comma-separated or fixed-length text files. It can be used to exchange data between Uniface and external tools such as spreadsheet applications.\">TXT</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532918\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532918\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "DBMS Connector Overview Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 16, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 DBMS Connector Overview This section provides an overview of supported functionality and limitations for all DBMS connectors. Each Uniface database connector is identified in Uniface by a 3-character mnemonic, and each one has its own set of limits, SQL scripts and utilities, and properties that you can configure using the DBMS options provided. For the supported platforms and product versions for your DBMS, refer to the Platform Availability Matrix . The connector mnemonic is used in assignment files to designate the connector version, the path to the connector, and the options to be used. For more information, see [DRIVER_SETTINGS] and Paths and Path Assignments . Table 1. Connector Mnemonics Connector Mnemonic Database DB2 DB2. For more information, see DB2 . INF Informix. For more information, see Informix . LDP LDAP Connector. For more information, see LDAP Connector . MSS Microsoft SQL Server. For more information, see Microsoft SQL Server . MQL MySQL. For more information, see MySQL . OD0, OD1, OD2 ODBC. For more information, see ODBC . ORA Oracle. For more information, see Oracle . PGS PostgreSQL. For more information, see PostgreSQL . SEQ Sequential. For more information, see Sequential . SLE SQLite. For more information, see SQLite . SYB Sybase. For more information, see Sybase . TXT Text. For more information, see TXT . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}